<paragraph blockId="2.[151,432,974,1037]" box="[151,248,1011,1037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">
<figureCitation box="[151,248,1011,1037]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStartId-0="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1392,179,1917]" captionTargetBox-1="[204,1383,181,1920]" captionTargetId-0="figure-20@3.[195,1392,179,1917]" captionTargetId-1="figure-22@4.[204,1383,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. West European colour form of Vespa crabro (USA: NC).A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Anterior view of head. D. Lateral view of pronotum. pnc = pronotal carina, pnl = pronotal lobe, ptc = pretegular carina. Scale bars: 1 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Japanese colour form of Vespa crabro specimen collected on Mayne Island, British Columbia, Canada. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Anterior view of head. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6671187" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6671191" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6671187/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6671191/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1078,2040]" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">
The specimen collected on Mayne Island (
<figureCitation box="[639,708,1078,1104]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[204,1383,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[204,1383,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Japanese colour form of Vespa crabro specimen collected on Mayne Island, British Columbia, Canada. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Lateral habitus. C. Anterior view of head. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6671191" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6671191/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) was identified morphologically by the authors as the Japanese colour form of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[326,475,1114,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crabro">
<emphasis box="[326,475,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">Vespa crabro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, formerly 
<taxonomicName authority="Cameron" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1903" box="[598,1012,1114,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="crabro" subSpecies="flavofasciata">
<emphasis box="[598,901,1114,1140]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">Vespa crabro flavofasciata</emphasis>
Cameron
</taxonomicName>
(following the taxon concepts of 
<bibRefCitation author="Archer, M. E." pageId="2" pageNumber="307" pagination="157 - 163" refId="ref6171" refString="Archer, M. E. (1992) The taxonomy of Vespa crabro L. and V. dybowskii Andre (Hym., Vespinae). The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 128, 157 - 163." type="journal article" year="1992">Archer 1992</bibRefCitation>
) which is native to 
<collectingCountry box="[483,550,1150,1176]" name="Japan" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[560,631,1150,1176]" name="South Korea" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">Korea</collectingCountry>
, and eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[775,850,1150,1176]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Archer, M. E." box="[864,1011,1150,1176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="307" pagination="157 - 163" refId="ref6171" refString="Archer, M. E. (1992) The taxonomy of Vespa crabro L. and V. dybowskii Andre (Hym., Vespinae). The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 128, 157 - 163." type="journal article" year="1992">Archer 1992</bibRefCitation>
). A 658 base pair (bp) sequence of the specimen (GenBank Accession 
<accessionNumber box="[513,636,1186,1212]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/OL702713" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">OL702713</accessionNumber>
) was 100% identical to 14 sequences of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1108,1213,1186,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Vespa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crabro">
<emphasis box="[1108,1213,1186,1212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">V. crabro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1286,1433,1186,1212]" name="South Korea" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">South Korea</collectingCountry>
: GenBank Accessions 
<accessionNumber box="[398,527,1221,1247]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MN716838" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">MN716838</accessionNumber>
– 
<accessionNumber box="[557,686,1221,1247]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MN716841" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">MN716841</accessionNumber>
and 
<accessionNumber box="[743,873,1221,1247]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MN609218" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">MN609218</accessionNumber>
– 
<accessionNumber box="[903,1032,1221,1247]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MN609227" pageId="2" pageNumber="307">MN609227</accessionNumber>
(see Discussion for details of these sequences), with an E-value of 0.0 and a bit score of 1214.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
